<tr>
<td style="padding: 5px 0px 5px 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; background-color: #0079c1; border: 1px solid #cccccc;" align="left" valign="middle">
<span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 16px; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold;">RESEARCH SUMMARIES</span>
<!-- END Research Summaries -->
<!-- START Story 1 -->
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0px 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; border-left: 1px solid #cccccc; border-right: 1px solid #cccccc;" valign="top">
<p><span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 26px; color: #0079c1; font-weight: bold;">Does pre-transplant clonal burden matter in myelodysplastic syndromes?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">In this review, the authors review data on disease burden and transplant outcomes in myelodysplastic syndromes (MDS), and describe which MDS patients may benefit most from allogeneic hematopoietic cell transplantation (HCT).</span></p>
<p><a style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #0079c1;" href="#">Read the full research summary</a></p>
</td>
</tr>
<!-- END Story 1 -->
<!-- START divider -->
<tr>
<td style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) none repeat scroll 0% 0%; border-bottom: 1px solid #cccccc; border-right: 1px solid #cccccc; border-left: 1px solid #cccccc; height: 1px; width: 100%; margin: 0px;"> </td>
</tr>
<!-- END divider -->
<!-- START Story 2 -->
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0px 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; border-right: 1px solid #cccccc; border-left: 1px solid #cccccc; border-bottom: 1px solid #cccccc;" align="left" valign="top">
<p><span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 26px; color: #0079c1; font-weight: bold;">Allo- better than auto-HCT for early relapsed/refractory follicular lymphoma</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">An analysis of 44 patients with early relapsed or refractory follicular lymphoma (FL) shows a significant difference in 3-year event-free survival (EFS) between allogeneic and autologous transplantation (80% vs. 42%, respectively; p<0.015), but only in patients with previous remission duration of ≤12 months. The authors concluded that “very early relapsed FL may warrant consideration of allogeneic over autologous transplantation in the appropriate setting.” </span></p>
<p><a style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #0079c1;" href="#">Read the full research summary</a></p>
</td>
</tr>
<!-- END Story 2 -->
<!-- START Story 3 -->
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0px 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; border-right: 1px solid #cccccc; border-left: 1px solid #cccccc; border-bottom: 1px solid #cccccc;" align="left" valign="top">
<p><span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 26px; color: #0079c1; font-weight: bold;">Improved quality of life, no GVHD after HCT in adults with sickle cell disease</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">HCT using an innovative conditioning regimen can result in a cure with marked improvements in quality of life for patients with high-risk sickle cell disease, according to a study of 13 adults transplanted using matched related donors.</span></p>
<p><a style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #0079c1;" href="#">Read the full research summary</a></p>
</td>
</tr>
<!-- END Story 3 -->
<!-- START Story 4 -->
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0px 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; border-right: 1px solid #cccccc; border-left: 1px solid #cccccc; border-bottom: 1px solid #cccccc;" align="left" valign="top">
<p><span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 26px; color: #0079c1; font-weight: bold;">Noteworthy research</span></p>
<p><a style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #0079c1;" href="#">Cardiomyopathy risk after HCT</a></p>
<p><a style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #0079c1;" href="#">HCT for mixed phenotype acute leukemia</a></p>
<p><a style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #0079c1;" href="#">Post-transplant thrombotic microangiopathy</a></p>
